---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Site Updates', url: '/site-updates' }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Site Updates - BreederHQ"
  description="Internal update log for the BreederHQ marketing website."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  noindex={true}
>
  <main>
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Site Updates
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          A running log of content changes to breederhq.com. Click any page link to review the change on the live site. Newest updates first.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-16">

        <!-- ========== May 27, 2026 - Parasite Program URL update in goat content articles ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 27, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Updated two long-form goat content articles to reference the Parasite Program at its new canonical URL. The in-app Parasite Program dashboard moved from <code>/herd-health/parasite-program</code> to <code>/herd/parasite-program</code> as part of the new Herd Management module home. The breederhq platform registers a client-side alias from the old path inside the SPA (in-app links and bookmarks redirect after the JS bundle boots, preserving any query string), so existing in-product links keep working. The article copy is updated to reflect the canonical path going forward.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Updated articles</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li><a href="/articles/goat-herd-health-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/articles/goat-herd-health-software</a></li>
            <li><a href="/articles/dairy-goat-record-keeping-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/articles/dairy-goat-record-keeping-software</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Notes</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            The public buyer-facing destination URL <code>/breeders/:tenantSlug/parasite-program</code> is unchanged. Only the authenticated breeder-side dashboard URL moved. No SEO impact expected (article copy references are code blocks describing internal paths, not crawlable links).
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 26, 2026 - Caprine service landing pages + provider acquisition ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 26, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched the consumer-facing and provider-acquisition surface for caprine (goat-specific) service categories on BreederHQ Marketplace. This is the follow-on to the backend-first slice that shipped the canonical catalog entries + i18n labels — public landing pages now exist so goat breeders can actually find these providers and providers can actually sign up under the right category.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New consumer pages (10)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li><a href="/services/caprine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/caprine-services</a> (umbrella)</li>
            <li><a href="/services/disbudding-tattoo" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/disbudding-tattoo</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/goat-hoof-trimming" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/goat-hoof-trimming</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/fecal-lab" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/fecal-lab</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/dhir-tester" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/dhir-tester</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/linear-appraisal-scheduling" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/linear-appraisal-scheduling</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/buck-service" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/buck-service</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/goat-ai-technician" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/goat-ai-technician</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/mobile-goat-vet" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/mobile-goat-vet</a></li>
            <li><a href="/services/goat-transport" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/goat-transport</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New provider-acquisition pages (10)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li><a href="/for-providers/caprine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/caprine-services</a> (umbrella)</li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/disbudding-tattoo" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/disbudding-tattoo</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/goat-hoof-trimming" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/goat-hoof-trimming</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/fecal-lab" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/fecal-lab</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/dhir-tester" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/dhir-tester</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/linear-appraisal-scheduling" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/linear-appraisal-scheduling</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/buck-service" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/buck-service</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/goat-ai-technician" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/goat-ai-technician</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/mobile-goat-vet" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/mobile-goat-vet</a></li>
            <li><a href="/for-providers/goat-transport" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/goat-transport</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Reciprocal cross-links</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            <a href="/services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services</a> now lists Caprine Services in the Equine &amp; Livestock Specialists section with four region-style chips deep-linking to the most-trafficked specialists. <a href="/services/livestock-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/livestock-services</a> &ldquo;Related&rdquo; grid now points to <a href="/services/caprine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/caprine-services</a> so goat breeders bouncing through the generic livestock surface land on the goat-specific one. <a href="/for-providers/livestock" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/livestock</a> gained a Related Provider Categories grid that links to the caprine umbrella. Every caprine consumer page links to its <code>/for-providers/&lt;category&gt;</code> peer and vice versa.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">SEO</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Each consumer page targets goat-specific specialist queries (&ldquo;goat hoof trimmer near me&rdquo;, &ldquo;dairy goat DHIR tester&rdquo;, &ldquo;goat AI technician&rdquo;, etc.) without faking provider counts or fabricating listings. Provider-acquisition pages emit BreadcrumbList + FAQPage schema via BaseLayout. Auto-included in the generated sitemap on next deploy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Marketplace dropdown</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Sibling change in the <code>breederhq</code> repo: the marketplace services-index dropdown (<code>CATEGORY_OPTIONS</code>) now includes the 10 caprine categories so the in-app browse and <code>/services/category/&lt;url-slug&gt;</code> routes resolve correctly. URL slugs come from the canonical catalog (e.g. <code>caprine-services</code>, <code>goat-hoof-trimming</code>, <code>goat-ai-technician</code>) — the catalog id and url slug intentionally diverge in a few cases for readability.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 17, 2026 - New provider-acquisition page: Equine Services ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 17, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">New provider-acquisition page at <a href="/for-providers/equine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine-services</a> targeting the broader equine services ecosystem: boarding facilities, horse trainers, riding instructors, breeding facilities, and equine service professionals. Positions BreederHQ Marketplace as structured discovery and trust infrastructure for the equine industry, distinct from the existing facility-focused <a href="/for-providers/equine" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine</a> page (which is arena/boarding-stall focused). New page covers why equine discovery is broken, why generic directories fail equine providers, facility and credential visibility, marketplace benefits, flat-fee pricing, verification, and a 7-question FAQ.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">SEO</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Targets &ldquo;equine services marketplace&rdquo;, &ldquo;horse boarding listing&rdquo;, &ldquo;advertise equine facility&rdquo;, and &ldquo;horse trainer directory&rdquo;. Emits BreadcrumbList and FAQPage schema via BaseLayout. Auto-included in the generated sitemap on next deploy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Internal links</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Bidirectional supply/demand wiring: links OUT to demand-side category pages (<a href="/services/equine-boarding" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/equine-boarding</a>, <a href="/services/farriers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/farriers</a>) in a dedicated &ldquo;Where Equine Clients Are Searching&rdquo; section, UP to <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a> from the Verification section as the credential explainer, and across to provider siblings (<a href="/for-providers/equine" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">equine</a>, <a href="/for-providers/boarding-facilities" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">boarding-facilities</a>, <a href="/for-providers/farrier" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">farrier</a>, <a href="/for-providers/training" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">training</a>, <a href="/for-providers/veterinary" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">veterinary</a>, <a href="/for-providers/transport" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">transport</a>) in the Related Provider Categories grid.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 17, 2026 - First geographic marketplace page: Lexington, KY equine boarding ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 17, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched the first city + service geographic marketplace page on BreederHQ at <a href="/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky</a>. This page is the prototype for the future geographic directory architecture (city + service) and is intentionally editorial, not templated. It leads with the Bluegrass equine ecosystem (Keeneland, the Kentucky Horse Park, Hagyard, Rood &amp; Riddle, the Inner Bluegrass karst pasture geology that drove Thoroughbred breeding to the region in the first place), walks through six concrete things to evaluate when boarding a horse in Lexington specifically (pasture stocking, fencing, biosecurity around sales weeks at Keeneland, freeze management, arena and trailer access, hospital proximity), and ships with a transparent &ldquo;featured providers coming soon&rdquo; placeholder rather than any fabricated listings or provider counts.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New file</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            <a href="/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky</a> (<code>src/pages/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky.astro</code>)
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Sections</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Hero (Horse Capital of the World framing, dual CTA to providers + featured listings anchor)</li>
            <li>Lexington Equine Ecosystem (Keeneland, Kentucky Horse Park, Hagyard, Rood &amp; Riddle, Park Equine, karst geology, supporting trades)</li>
            <li>What To Look For in Boarding in Lexington (six evaluation criteria, written for horse owners, not generic pet owners)</li>
            <li>Featured Providers placeholder (explicit no-fake-listings note)</li>
            <li>Nearby Areas (Versailles, Georgetown, Paris, Nicholasville, Winchester, Richmond, Midway, Frankfort)</li>
            <li>FAQ (six Lexington-specific questions, used for FAQPage schema)</li>
            <li>Provider CTA + Related-on-BreederHQ link block</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">SEO</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Targets &ldquo;horse boarding Lexington KY&rdquo;, &ldquo;equine boarding Lexington&rdquo;, and &ldquo;horse boarding Bluegrass region&rdquo;. Emits BreadcrumbList, FAQPage, and Service schema via BaseLayout. Auto-included in the generated sitemap on next deploy.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Internal links</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Cross-links to <a href="/services/equine-boarding" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/equine-boarding</a> (parent category hub), <a href="/for-providers/equine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine-services</a> (provider acquisition), and <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a>. Also links to <code>/services/farriers/kentucky</code> as a forward-looking placeholder for the upcoming regional farrier directory.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 17, 2026 - Trust & Verification page launched at /trust ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 17, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched the foundational BreederHQ Marketplace trust and verification page at <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a>. This page is the canonical explainer for how identity, credentials, and reviews are verified on the marketplace, and how a breeder-focused trust system differs from Yelp, Rover, and Thumbtack. It targets both buyer and provider audiences with separate CTAs and is intentionally hedged (uses language like "supports", "designed to", "providers may submit") so it does not over-promise on verification workflows that are still expanding.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New file</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a> (<code>src/pages/trust.astro</code>)
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Page sections</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Hero introducing trust infrastructure</li>
            <li>Why Trust Matters in Animal Services</li>
            <li>Verification Tiers (ID Verified, Verified, Accredited)</li>
            <li>Credential Verification Examples (CPDT-KA, IAABC, AFA, USDA, AKC Breeder of Merit, equine certifications, insurance, breed clubs)</li>
            <li>How Reviews Work (verified transactions, no paid removal, public response, no retaliatory reviews)</li>
            <li>Why BreederHQ Is Different from Yelp, Rover, or Thumbtack (side-by-side table)</li>
            <li>FAQ (8 questions, wired into FAQPage schema)</li>
            <li>Provider CTA (List Your Services, with cross-links to farriers, equine services, training, veterinary)</li>
            <li>Consumer CTA (Browse the Marketplace, with cross-links to buyer guides and the /services/farriers and /services/equine-boarding category pages)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Schema emitted</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>BreadcrumbList</strong> via BaseLayout breadcrumbs prop</li>
            <li><strong>FAQPage</strong> via BaseLayout faqs prop</li>
            <li><strong>Article</strong> via BaseLayout article prop (datePublished 2026-05-17, author BreederHQ)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Navigation updated</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Added "Trust &amp; Verification" link in <code>HeaderV2.astro</code> in four locations: desktop Buyers mega-menu (Getting Started column), desktop Service Providers mega-menu (Resources column, replacing the old <code>/for-providers#trust</code> fragment anchor), mobile Buyers accordion, and mobile Service Providers accordion. The page is reachable from both buyer and provider entry points.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Sitemap</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            <code>@astrojs/sitemap</code> auto-generates sitemap-index.xml at build time, so <code>/trust</code> will be picked up automatically on the next deploy. No manual sitemap edits required.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 17, 2026 - New flagship category landing page: /services/equine-boarding ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 17, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">New flagship category landing page at <a href="/services/equine-boarding" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/equine-boarding</a>, establishing BreederHQ Marketplace as an equine-service discovery platform (not generic pet boarding). The page is the parent hub for the geographic equine-boarding pages and lives at the canonical <code>/services/</code> path. Tone is equine-native, operationally knowledgeable, and facility-aware throughout. No fake provider counts, no fabricated listings.</p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New file</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            <code>src/pages/services/equine-boarding.astro</code>
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Sections</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li>Hero framing equine boarding as a high-stakes operational decision (1,000-pound athletes, seasonal cycling, hoof-care cadence, forage-sensitive digestion)</li>
            <li>Types of Equine Boarding: pasture board, full care, self care, training facilities, breeding facilities, retirement and rehabilitation board</li>
            <li>What to Look For in a Boarding Facility: fencing and footing, turnout program, hay and feed quality, water, biosecurity and quarantine, fire and emergency plan, veterinary relationship, farrier coordination, staff coverage, boarding contract</li>
            <li>Facility Features: indoor and outdoor arenas, round pen, hot and cold wash stalls, heated tack room, individual and group turnout, trailer parking, trail access, cross-country schooling, foaling stalls and cameras, on-site veterinary</li>
            <li>Boarding Cost Factors: level of care, region and land cost, hay and grain inclusion, turnout time, facility amenities, add-on services, training and lessons</li>
            <li>Regional Equine Hubs: Ocala, Wellington, Lexington, Aiken, Scottsdale, Weatherford / Fort Worth, Temecula / San Diego, Middleburg</li>
            <li>FAQ (8 questions, wired into FAQPage schema)</li>
            <li>Provider CTA linking to <a href="/for-providers/equine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine-services</a> and <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">SEO</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Targets &ldquo;horse boarding near me&rdquo;, &ldquo;equine boarding&rdquo;, &ldquo;horse boarding facilities&rdquo;, &ldquo;pasture board&rdquo;, and &ldquo;full care horse boarding&rdquo;. Emits BreadcrumbList, FAQPage, and Service structured data via BaseLayout schema props. Auto-included in the generated sitemap on next build.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Internal links</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Cross-links to <a href="/horses" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/horses</a>, <a href="/services/farriers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/farriers</a>, <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a>, and <a href="/for-providers/equine-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/for-providers/equine-services</a>.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- ========== May 17, 2026 - Flagship marketplace category landing page: Farriers ========== -->
        <article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 17, 2026</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched the flagship BreederHQ Marketplace category landing page for farriers at <a href="/services/farriers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/services/farriers</a>. This is the prototype for the future <code>/services/&lt;category&gt;</code> directory pattern, alongside the recently shipped Lexington equine boarding geo page. It is buyer-facing, equine-native, and intentionally ships with placeholder featured-provider cards rather than any fabricated listings, reviews, or provider counts.</p>

